==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*tanþ-, *tunþ-'', from Indo-European ''*h₁dont-'' ‘tooth’.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian [[toth|tōth]], Old Saxon [[tand]] (Dutch [[tand]]), Old High German [[zan]], [[zand]] (German [[Zahn]]), Old Norse [[tǫnn]] (Swedish [[tand]]), Gothic [[𐍄𐌿𐌽𐌸𐌿𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Sanskrit [[दन्त]] (Hindi [[दांत़]]), Greek [[οδών|ὀδών]], Latin [[dens]] (French [[dent]]), Old Irish [[dēt]], Lithuanian [[dantis|dantìs]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /to:θ/

===Noun===
'''tōþ'''
# a [[tooth]]

